{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:50:39.878955+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The GitHub token doesn't have write permissions to push changes to this repository. Let me note the limitation and provide the complete implementation plan.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n### Issue #1: \"Add release notes page\"\n\n**What was requested:** Add a release notes page for version 1.1 and expose it in the sidebar.\n\n### Current State\n\n1. **`docs/release-notes.md`** — Already exists with the correct content:\n   ```markdown\n   ---\n   id: release-notes\n   title: Release Notes\n   ---\n   \n   # Release Notes\n   \n   Release notes for version 1.1 will be documented here.\n   ```\n\n2. **`sidebars.js`** — Does **not** include `release-notes` in the sidebar. Current content:\n   ```js\n   module.exports = {\n     tutorialSidebar: [\n       'intro',\n       'getting-started',\n       'installation',\n       'versioning'\n     ]\n   };\n   ```\n\n### Required Change\n\nOnly **one file** needs to be updated: **`sidebars.js`**. The `'release-notes'` entry must be added to the `tutorialSidebar` array.\n\n**Updated `sidebars.js`:**\n```js\nmodule.exports = {\n  tutorialSidebar: [\n    'intro',\n    'getting-started',\n    'installation',\n    'versioning',\n    'release-notes'\n  ]\n};\n```\n\n### CI Notes\n\nThe file `.github/ci_notes.txt` referenced in the issue comment does not exist in the repository. The validation script (`scripts/validate_repo.py`) checks that required files exist (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `package.json`, `docusaurus.config.js`, `sidebars.js`, `docs/intro.md`) and that JS configs export properly via `module.exports`. The updated `sidebars.js` will continue to pass these checks since `module.exports` is preserved and all required files remain in place.\n\n### Limitation\n\n**Both `create_or_update_file` and `push_files` tool calls failed with HTTP 403 (\"Resource not accessible by personal access token\").** The token used for th